# React Native Web Project

This is a **design system mobile-first app** built with React Native for Web, primarily displayed at mobile screen size.

## Stack

- **Expo SDK 55** (managed workflow) with **Expo Router** (file-based routing, root: `./src/app`)
- **React Native 0.83** + **react-native-web ~0.21** — Expo handles aliasing and bundling automatically
- **Metro** bundler for all platforms (NOT webpack) — configured in `metro.config.js`
- **NativeWind v4** + **Tailwind CSS 3** for styling — use `className` prop, NOT inline `StyleSheet.create`
- **class-variance-authority (cva)** for component variants
- **Storybook 10** via `@storybook/react-native-web-vite` for component development
- **React 19** + **TypeScript 5.9** (strict mode)

## Key Conventions

- Entry point: `expo-router/entry` (not a custom index)
- Utility function `cn()` from `@/lib/cn` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for merging class names
- UI kit components live in `src/components/ui-kit/` with barrel export in `index.ts`
- Each UI kit component has a colocated `.stories.tsx` file
- Theme colors defined in `tailwind.config.js` (primary, neutral, surface, content palettes)
- Legacy theme constants in `src/constants/theme.ts` (Colors, Fonts, MaxContentWidth)
- Hooks in `src/hooks/`, utilities in `src/lib/`

## Platform-Specific Files

Use `.web.tsx` / `.web.ts` suffix for web-specific implementations. Expo/Metro resolves them automatically:

- `animated-icon.web.tsx` / `animated-icon.tsx` (native)
- `app-tabs.web.tsx` / `app-tabs.tsx` (native)
- `use-color-scheme.web.ts` / `use-color-scheme.ts` (native)

For minor differences, use `Platform.OS === 'web'` checks instead of separate files.

## Do NOT

- Do NOT add webpack config — Metro handles web bundling
- Do NOT use `StyleSheet.create` for new components — use NativeWind `className`
- Do NOT import from `react-native-web` directly — always import from `react-native`
- Do NOT install packages without checking Expo SDK 55 compatibility
- Do NOT create `.native.tsx` files — the default (unsuffixed) file IS the native version
